          <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">4. HIRING AND RETURNING BIKES</h4><br>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">4.1 You may unlock a bike by scanning the QR code on the lock of the bike. If
            you are unable to scan the QR code successfully for whatever reason, you may alternatively enter the bikes
            identification number to unlock the bike. The bikes identification number is on both sides of the bike and
            starts with 17. </p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">4.2 When you have finished riding the bike, you may park it at any of the
            recognised public cycle parking spaces identified on our map. If a bike is not parked in one of these
            identified spaces then it is either deemed mis-parked or lost. You must park your bike in a tidy,
            unobtrusive manner.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">4.3 To park the bike, place it next to a bike rack, engage the lock and tap on
            End Journey on the App.</p><br>

          <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">5. BIKE USAGE CHARGES</h4><br>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">5.1 You must have a minimum of €1 credit on your e-wallet or have a valid
