          <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">6. MEMBERSHIPS</h4><br>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.1 Memberships allow the member up to four
            rides a day and up to one hour each. </p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.2 If you exceed this daily allowance as a member, you will be charged €1 per
            hour in accordance with our standard usage fee.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.3 You may purchase a €5 Day Pass, which allows for 12 hours usage for
            €5. </p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.4 The annual memberships and the Day Pass shall commence at
            the point of purchase.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.5 The annual memberships and the Day Pass shall
            automatically expire at the end of the relevant period. Upon expiration, you continue to be a registered
            user and have the option to purchase another membership or Day Pass.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">6.6 You may cancel your membership to the BleeperBike service at any time
            within 14 days of first becoming a member. If you cancel your membership early, we will deduct our fees for
            your use up to the point of cancellation, calculated on the basis of our standard €1 per hour fee. No
            refund will be given in respect of any cancellation after this 14 day period.</p><br>

          <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">7. PERIOD OF USE</h4><br>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">7.1 BleeperBike should not be used for more than 24 consecutive hours. 24
            consecutive hours is the maximum period of use.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">7.2 You must park and lock the BleeperBike at a recognised public cycle
            parking prior to the end of the maximum period of use.</p>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">7.3 The bike is deemed lost and Charges shall apply should the maximum period
            of use be exceeded.</p><br>

          <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">8. BIKE FAULTS</h4><br>

          <p class="list-group-item-text">8.1 We ask that you carry out a visual inspection of the bike before unlocking
